Certainly! I'll guide you through each of these steps using shell commands and provide you with an example of the HTML and JavaScript code needed for your interactive game.

### Step 1: Create a Directory and Navigate into It
First, open your terminal or command prompt and run the following commands:

```bash
# Create a directory named "game"
mkdir game

# Navigate into the "game" directory
cd game
```

### Step 2: Create a File Named "index.html"
In the terminal, run the following command to create the `index.html` file:

```bash
# Create a file named "index.html"
touch index.html
```

### Step 3: Add HTML Code to "index.html"
Open the `index.html` file in your favorite text editor and add the following HTML code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Antonym Game</title>
    <style>
        .word {
            text-decoration: underline;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Antonym Rearrangement Game</h1>
    <p>Click on the underlined word to reveal the word you need to find an antonym for.</p>
    <p>The word is: <span class="word" id="word"></span></p>
    <input type="text" id="answer" placeholder="Enter antonym here">
    <button onclick="checkAnswer()">Submit</button>
    <p id="feedback"></p>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Step 4: Add JavaScript Code to Handle Interactivity
Create a new file named `script.js` in the same directory and add the following JavaScript code:

```javascript
// script.js

// Example words and their antonyms
const words = [
    { word: "happy", antonym: "sad" },
    { word: "hot", antonym: "cold" },
    { word: "light", antonym: "dark" }
];

// Pick a random word from the list
const randomWord = words[Math.floor(Math.random() * words.length)];

// Display the word with letters scrambled
const scrambledWord = randomWord.word.split('').sort(() => Math.random() - 0.5).join('');
document.getElementById('word').innerText = scrambledWord;

// Function to check the user's answer
function checkAnswer() {
    const userAnswer = document.getElementById('answer').value.toLowerCase();
    const feedbackElement = document.getElementById('feedback');

    if (userAnswer === randomWord.antonym) {
        feedbackElement.textContent = "Correct! The antonym is " + randomWord.antonym + ".";
        feedbackElement.style.color = "green";
    } else {
        feedbackElement.textContent = "Incorrect. Try again.";
        feedbackElement.style.color = "red";
    }
}

// Reveal the word when clicked
document.getElementById('word').addEventListener('click', function() {
    this.innerText = randomWord.word;
});
```

### Explanation
- **HTML and CSS**: The HTML file contains a clickable word, input field, and button for user interaction. Basic styles are added for visual clarity.
- **JavaScript**: The script selects a random word and scrambles it for display. When the user submits their answer, it checks against the correct antonym and provides feedback. Clicking the word reveals the unscrambled word.

You can run this HTML file in a browser to see your interactive antonym game in action. Adjust the word list and styles as needed to customize the game further.
